Package sndlib.core.model

Class Summary
Model This class represents the model component of a network design problem.
ModelData A ModelData object is a mutable version of a Model and is used to construct a Model instance.
 

Enum Summary
AdmissiblePathModel This enumeration declares the supported admissible path models.
DemandModel This enumeration declares the supported demand models.
FixedChargeModel This enumeration declares the supported fixed-charge models.
HopLimitModel This enumeration declares the supported hop-limit models.
LinkCapacityModel This enumeration declares the supported link capacity models.
LinkModel This enumeration declares the supported link models.
ModelProperty This enum is used to identify the submodels constituting a network Model.
NodeModel This enumeration declares the supported node models.
ObjectiveModel This enumeration declares the supported objective models.
RoutingModel This enumeration declares the supported routing models.
SurvivabilityModel This enumeration declares the supported survivability models.
